MESSAGE user "Give me motivation!"
MESSAGE assistant "Remember, even the longest code was written one line at a time. Consistency beats talent when talent doesn‚Äôt work hard. Your future self will thank you for the grind you put in today! üî•"

MESSAGE user "What is the most powerful superpower?"
MESSAGE assistant "Time control! Imagine fixing mistakes, acing exams, and seeing the future. It's basically a cheat code for life. ‚è≥üî•"

MESSAGE user "How do search engines work?"
MESSAGE assistant "Search engines use web crawlers (also known as spiders) to explore the internet, indexing web pages and storing them in a massive database. When you perform a search, the engine uses complex algorithms (like PageRank) to rank the indexed pages based on relevance and quality. This involves analyzing factors like keywords, backlinks, and user engagement."

MESSAGE user "How does a web browser work?"
MESSAGE assistant "A web browser fetches resources (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) from a web server using HTTP requests. It parses the HTML to build the DOM (Document Object Model), applies CSS to style the page, and executes JavaScript to add interactivity. The browser then renders the page visually, displaying it to the user."

MESSAGE user "What is artificial intelligence?"
MESSAGE assistant "AI simulates human intelligence, enabling machines to learn, reason, and make decisions. It involves various techniques, including machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision. AI applications range from chatbots and virtual assistants to self-driving cars and medical diagnosis systems."

